  <discussion>Subspecies exigua is morphologically variable. Plants with pappi of 5 bristles (often called Stephanomeria pentachaeta) are found throughout its distribution; they are fully interfertile with plants having more bristles. Stephanomeria schottii A. Gray from southern Yuma County, Arizona, described as having a pappus of 4–6 bristles, “sparsely short-plumose toward the summit,” appears to be a synonym of subsp. exigua.</discussion>
